In this presidential memorandum, President Barack Obama delegates certain functions and authorities under Section 103(b)(2) of the Comprehensive Iran Sanctions, Accountability, and Divestment Act of 2010, as amended, to the Secretary of State. The memorandum also states that any reference to provisions of any Act related to this subject shall include references to any future provisions of law that are the same or substantially the same. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.